<h1>PipeDream:!ReadMe</h1>

<p>This directory contains most of PipeDream's application resources.</p>

<h4>!ReadMe</h4>
<p>
This file explains the purpose of the files in this directory.
Most of these files are critical to the operation of PipeDream
and so should not be deleted or modified without due consideration and care.
</p>

<h4>Neutral</h4>
<p>Directory containing non-localised resources.</p>

<h4>Neutral.Markers</h4>
<p>Directory containing non-localised image files used as series point markers in charts.</p>

<h4>Neutral.Pictures</h4>
<p>Directory containing non-localised image files used to fill bars in bar charts.</p>

<h4>Neutral.RISC_OS</h4>
<p>Directory containing non-localised RISC OS-specific resources.</p>

<h4>Neutral.RISC_OS.!Sprite</h4>
<p>Compressed sprite file displayed as the main image on the splash screen.</p>

<h4>Neutral.RISC_OS.BuildVer</h4>
<p>Text file containing information about this build (application and compiler versions).</p>

<h4>Neutral.RISC_OS.ImageSlot</h4>
<p>
Utility to set the Window Manager slot size appropriately for a RISC OS application executable from its size and AIF header information.
Replaces *WimpSlot in the application's !Run file.
</p>

<h4>Neutral.RISC_OS.Loader</h4>
<p>BASIC program that sets some PipeDream$xxx variables.</p>

<h4>Neutral.RISC_OS.Splash</h4>
<p>BASIC program that displays a splash screen.</p>

<h4>Neutral.RISC_OS.SprCht</h4>
<p>Chart icon sprites - low resolution (rectangular pixel, pixel sizes x = 2, y = 4 OS units).</p>

<h4>Neutral.RISC_OS.SprCht22</h4>
<p>Chart icon sprites - standard resolution (square pixel, pixel size 2 OS units).</p>

<h4><em>Country</em></h4>
<p>Country-specific directory containing localised resources.</p>

<h4><em>Country</em>.PDrivers</h4>
<p>Directory containing localised printer definition files.</p>

<h4><em>Country</em>.Templates</h4>
<p>Directory containing localised template files.</p>

<h4><em>Country</em>.RISC_OS</h4>
<p>Directory containing localised RISC OS-specific resources.</p>

<h4><em>Country</em>.RISC_OS.Help.HTML</h4>
<p>Directory containing help files in HTML format that are displayed if a browser is present.</p>

<h4><em>Country</em>.RISC_OS.Help.Text</h4>
<p>Text file displayed as trivial help if no browser is present to display the HTML help.</p>

<h4><em>Country</em>.RISC_OS.Messages</h4>
<p>Text files that are used to look up localised textual messages from language-independent tags and internal error numbers.</p>

<h4><em>Country</em>.RISC_OS.Sprites</h4>
<p>Toolbar and button sprites - lowest resolution (rectangular pixel, pixel sizes x = 2, y = 4 OS units).</p>

<h4><em>Country</em>.RISC_OS.Sprites11</h4>
<p>Toolbar and button sprites - highest resolution (square pixel, pixel size 1 OS unit).</p>

<h4><em>Country</em>.RISC_OS.Sprites22</h4>
<p>Toolbar and button sprites - standard resolution (square pixel, pixel size 2 OS units).</p>

<h4><em>Country</em>.RISC_OS.WTemplates</h4>
<p>Directory containing localised window template files.</p>

<h4>UK</h4>
<p>
Country-specific directory containing localised resources for the United Kingdom.<br>
This is also used as the fallback directory for resources when no localised ones are found.
</p>

<h4>UK.CmdFiles</h4>
<p>Directory containing localised command example files for the United Kingdom.</p>

<h4>UK.DictDefn</h4>
<p>Directory containing dictionary definition files for the United Kingdom.</p>

<h4>UK.DictDefn.English</h4>
<p>Dictionary definition file allowing just characters A to Z in words.</p>

<h4>UK.DictDefn.Latin1</h4>
<p>Dictionary definition file allowing all Latin-1 alphabetic characters in words.</p>

<h4>UK.Dicts</h4>
<p>Directory containing the master dictionary for the United Kingdom.</p>

</body>
</html>
